subsection.p:
The magnitude of weight of an object near Earth, is very nearly independent of the object's distance from Earth. If the mass of the object is  m , then magnitude of weight is

	\text{Magnitude of weight, } W= m\, g, \ \ \ \text{ near Earth's surface,}

where  g  is called acceleration due to gravity, which has a standard value  9.81 \text{ m/s}^2.
